In a statement, the Vice President acknowledges the one-year anniversary of the devastating earthquake and tsunami that struck Japan in 2011. He remembers the lives lost and missing, and praises the resilience and fortitude of the Japanese people in the face of such a disaster. The Vice President had visited Japan five months after the event and witnessed the progress in rebuilding efforts. He also mentions the assistance provided by the American people through Operation Tomodachi, a relief effort that provided aid and supplies to those affected. The Vice President assures that the United States will continue to support Japan in their rebuilding process.